content.value: The 85th PMO Christmas Show. This show was performed at Purdue in December 2018 and aired on PBS in December 2019
The 84th PMO Christmas Show. This show was performed at Purdue in December 2017 and aired on PBS in December 2018
The 82nd PMO Christmas Show. This show was performed at Purdue in December 2015 and aired on PBS in December 2016
The 83rd PMO Christmas Show, featuring the Purdue All American Marching Band! This show was performed at Purdue in December 2016 and aired on PBS in December 2017

In 2018, I was incredible fortunate to have been given an opportunity to fly from Purdue to Cape Canaveral to sing at the gala and ceremony for the commissioning of the USS Indiana, the US Navy's newest (at the time) submarine.
This video is a compilation of all the songs we sang. The next morning, we sang the star spangled banner again at the ceremony.
The video quality is pretty low as it was filmed using a cell phone, but the audio quality is much better.
The
Christmas
show was my junior year in Great Expectations. We saw continued success that was started the year prior with
Monopoly
, but this time, bringing holiday cheer to show choir competitions year round. For a list of songs in this show and competitions we performed at, visit
showchoir.com
Garden of Eden
was my first show I performed with Twinsburg Great Expectations. For a list of the songs in this show and competitions we performed at, visit
showchoir.com
I performed in the
Monopoly

show my sophomore year at THS. Due to a variety of factors, this was the year GE started to gain visibility nationally. We won four of the six competitions we competed at that year. We also competed in Los Alamitos, California against choirs like Burroughs and Burbank and placed third. To learn more about this show, visit
showchoir.com
